pli":"Idamavoca bhagavā. ","eng":"That is what the Buddha said. ","html":"<p>{}"},"sn14.16:8.2":{"pli":"Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: ","eng":"Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: ","html":"{}</p>"},"sn14.16:9.1":{"pli":"“Saṃsaggā vanatho jāto, ","eng":"“Socializing creates a snarl; ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"These verses appear in a similar context at <a href='index.html?q=iti78#6.1'>Iti 78:6.1</a>. "},"sn14.16:9.2":{"pli":"asaṃsaggena chijjati; ","eng":"they’re cut off by being aloof. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn14.16:9.3":{"pli":"Parittaṃ dārumāruyha, ","eng":"If you’re lost in the middle of a great sea, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn14.16:9.4":{"pli":"yathā sīde mahaṇṇave. ","eng":"and you clamber up on a little log, you’ll sink. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn14.16:10.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ kusītamāgamma, ","eng":"So too, a person who lives well ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn14.16:10.2":{"pli":"sādhujīvipi sīdati; ","eng":"sinks by relying on a lazy person. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn14.16:10.3":{"pli":"Tasmā taṃ parivajjeyya, ","eng":"Hence you should avoid such ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn14.16:10.4":{"pli":"kusītaṃ hīnavīriyaṃ. ","eng":"a lazy person who lacks energy. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn14.16:11.1":{"pli":"Pavivittehi ariyehi, ","eng":"Dwell with the noble ones ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn14.16:11.2":{"pli":"pahitattehi jhāyīhi; ","eng":"who are secluded and determined ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn14.16:11.3":{"pli":"Niccaṃ āraddhavīriyehi, ","eng":"and always energetic; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn14.16:11.4":{"pli":"paṇḍitehi sahāvase”ti. ","eng":"the astute who practice absorption.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"sn14.16:11.5":{"pli":"Chaṭṭhaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"sn14.17":{"sn14.17:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 14.17 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 14.17 ","html":"<article id='sn14.17'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn14.17:0.2":{"pli":"2. Dutiyavagga ","eng":"Chapter Two ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn14.17:0.3":{"pli":"Assaddhasaṃsandanasutta ","eng":"Faithless ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn14.17:1.1":{"pli":"Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. ","eng":"At Sāvatthī. ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn14.17:1.2":{"pli":"“Dhātusova, bhikkhave, sattā saṃsandanti samenti. ","eng":"“Mendicants, sentient beings join together and converge because of an element: ","html":"<p>{}"},"sn14.17:1.3":{"pli":"Assaddhā assaddhehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the faithless with the faithless, ","html":"{}"},"sn14.17:1.4":{"pli":"ahirikā ahirikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the unconscientious with the unconscientious, ","html":"{}"},"sn14.17:1.5":{"pli":"anottappino anottappīhi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the imprudent with the imprudent, ","html":"{}"},"sn14.17:1.6":{"pli":"appassutā appassutehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the unlearned with the unlearned, ","html":"{}"},"sn14.17:1.7":{"pli":"kusītā kusītehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the lazy with the lazy, ","html":"{}"},"sn14.17:1.8":{"pli":"muṭṭhassatino muṭṭhassatīhi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the unmindful with the unmindful, ","html":"{}"},"sn14.17:1.9":{"pli":"duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti. ","eng":"and the witless with the witless. ","html":"{}</p>"},"sn14.17:2.1":{"pli":"Atītampi kho, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu. ","eng":"In the past, too, sentient beings came together and converged because of an element. … ","html":"<p>{}"},"sn14.17:2.2":{"pli":"Assaddhā assaddhehi saddhiṃ saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu; ","html":"{}"},"sn14.17:2.3":{"pli":"ahirikā ahirikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu; ","ht