.1":{"pli":"Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. ","eng":"At Sāvatthī. ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn14.19:1.2":{"pli":"“Dhātusova …pe… ","eng":"“Mendicants, sentient beings join together and converge because of an element: ","html":"<p data-counter='1'>{}"},"sn14.19:1.3":{"pli":"ahirikā ahirikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, anottappino anottappīhi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; hirimanā hirimanehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, ottappino ottappīhi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti …pe…. ","eng":"the unconscientious with the unconscientious … imprudent … witless. The conscientious with the conscientious … prudent … wise. ","html":"{}</p>"},"sn14.19:2.1":{"pli":"Ahirikā ahirikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, appassutā appassutehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; hirimanā hirimanehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, bahussutā bahussutehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti …pe…. ","eng":"… shameless … unlearned … witless. The conscientious with the conscientious … learned … wise. ","html":"<p data-counter='2'>{}</p>"},"sn14.19:3.1":{"pli":"Ahirikā ahirikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, kusītā kusītehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; hirimanā hirimanehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, āraddhavīriyā āraddhavīriyehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti …pe…. ","eng":"… shameless … lazy … witless. The conscientious with the conscientious … energetic … wise. ","html":"<p data-counter='3'>{}</p>"},"sn14.19:4.1":{"pli":"Ahirikā ahirikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, muṭṭhassatino muṭṭhassatīhi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; hirimanā hirimanehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, upaṭṭhitassatino upaṭṭhitassatīhi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti, paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samentī”ti …pe…. ","eng":"… shameless … unmindful … witless. The conscientious with the conscientious … mindful … wise.” ","html":"<p data-counter='4'>{}</p>"},"sn14.19:4.2":{"pli":"Navamaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"sn14.2":{"sn14.2:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 14.2 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 14.2 ","html":"<article id='sn14.2'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn14.2:0.2":{"pli":"1. Nānattavagga ","eng":"1. Diversity ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn14.2:0.3":{"pli":"Phassanānattasutta ","eng":"Diversity of Contacts ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn14.2:1.1":{"pli":"Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. ","eng":"At Sāvatthī. ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn14.2:1.2":{"pli":"“Dhātunānattaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ. ","eng":"“Mendicants, diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts. ","html":"<p>{}","comm":"The use of the word <i lang='pi' translate='no'>paṭicca</i> here connects back to dependent origination. Narrowing in on the particulars of sense experience, the text shows that particular factors give rise to other correlated factors, i.e. “this gives rise to this” (<a href='index.html?q=sn12.37#2.2'>SN 12.37:2.2</a>). "},"sn14.2:1.3":{"pli":"Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ? ","eng":"And what is the diversity of elements? ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:1.4":{"pli":"Cakkhudhātu sotadhātu ghānadhātu jivhādhātu kāyadhātu manodhātu—","eng":"The eye element, ear element, nose element, tongue element, body element, and mind element. ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:1.5":{"pli":"idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ. ","eng":"This is called the diversity of elements. ","html":"{}</p>"},"sn14.2:2.1":{"pli":"Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ? ","eng":"And how does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of contacts? ","html":"<p>{}"},"sn14.2:2.2":{"pli":"Cakkhudhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati cakkhusamphasso. ","eng":"The eye element gives rise to eye contact. ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.3":{"pli":"Sotadhātuṃ paṭicca … ","eng":"The ear element … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.4":{"pli":"ghānadhātuṃ paṭicca … ","eng":"nose … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.5":{"pli":"jivhādhātuṃ paṭicca … ","eng":"tongue … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.6":{"pli":"kāyadhātuṃ paṭicca … ","eng":"body … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.7":{"pli":"manodhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati manosamphasso. ","eng":"The mind element gives rise to mind contact. ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.8":{"pli":"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattan”ti. ","eng":"That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts.” ","html":"{}</p>"},"sn14.2:2.9":{"pli":"Dutiyaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"sn14.20":{"sn14.20:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 14.20 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 14.20 ","html":"<article id='sn14.20'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn14.20:0.2":{"pli":"2. Dutiyavagga ","eng":"Chapter Two ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn14.20:0.3":{"pli":"Anottappamūlakasutta ","eng":"Beginning With Imprudence ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn14.20:1.1":{"pli":"Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. ","eng":"At Sāvatthī. ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn14.20:1.2":{"pli":"“Dhātusova, bhikkhave, sattā saṃsandanti samenti. ","eng":"“Mendicants, sentient beings join together and converge because of an element: ","html":"<p data-counter='1'>{}"},"sn14.20:1.3":{"pli":"Anottappino anottappīhi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the imprudent with the imprudent … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.20:1.4":{"pli":"appassutā appassutehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; ","eng":"unlearned … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.20:1.5":{"pli":"duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; ","eng":"witless. ","html":"{}"},"sn14.20:1.6":{"pli":"ottappino ottappīhi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; ","eng":"The prudent with the prudent … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.20:1.7":{"pli":"bahussutā bahussutehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti; paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti …pe…. ","eng":"learned … wise. ","ht